WEBVTT

01:06.901 --> 01:09.036
Come on.

01:09.070 --> 01:10.337
- Simon.
- <i>Hello?</i>

01:10.370 --> 01:13.808
Did you put the poster of Harry
and the penguin in my office?

01:13.841 --> 01:16.676
- <i>Yeah. Shall I...</i>
- Get it out! Thank you.

01:16.711 --> 01:18.678
That campaign was
a complete disaster,

01:18.713 --> 01:21.716
and I don't need reminding
that his image needs

01:21.749 --> 01:23.483
a complete overhaul.

01:23.517 --> 01:24.384
<i>Uh, okay.</i>

01:24.417 --> 01:26.087
And can someone please
explain to Harry

01:26.120 --> 01:27.654
if he wants to
be a humanitarian,

01:27.687 --> 01:29.623
he has to save humans,
not penguins.

01:29.656 --> 01:30.657
<i>I'll contact...</i>

01:38.532 --> 01:41.635
<i>WNN brings you this
report on the orphan refugee crisis.</i>

01:41.668 --> 01:43.738
<i>Live from the
Ukbar-Georgia border.</i>

01:45.472 --> 01:46.774
<i>We go to Mark Phillips.</i>

01:46.808 --> 01:48.843
<i>Where is this world's
conscience?</i>

01:56.818 --> 01:59.586
Matt, Kate. Kate.

01:59.619 --> 02:02.522
Stop talking.
I've... I've had an idea.

02:02.556 --> 02:06.027
Top secret, but I've, uh,
found a campaign to put Harry onto.

02:06.060 --> 02:08.428
There's a war in, um,

02:08.930 --> 02:10.832
Georgia and Ukbar,

02:10.865 --> 02:13.600
wherever the hell that is,
that literally no one gives a shit about.

02:13.633 --> 02:17.038
It's got everything.
Refugees, landmines, orphans, white people.

02:17.071 --> 02:19.040
So, I wanna
put on a concert.

02:19.073 --> 02:21.876
The biggest peace concert the world
has ever seen, bigger than Live 8,

02:21.909 --> 02:24.411
and we'll have Katy Perry,
Ed Sheeran,

02:24.444 --> 02:27.581
Beyonce,
and Harry topping the bill.

02:27.614 --> 02:29.583
This is gonna take him
to the next level.

02:29.616 --> 02:31.018
What do you say?

02:31.052 --> 02:33.988
Do you wanna join me
in changing the world?

02:34.021 --> 02:36.023
<i>This is Matt
from Dim Sum Now.</i>

02:36.057 --> 02:38.726
Sorry, wrong number.
Yeah, um, Matt from, yeah,

02:38.759 --> 02:41.695
can I have the pork dumplings

02:41.729 --> 02:44.397
and, um, some spring rolls?

02:44.431 --> 02:46.433
Thanks so much.
Thank you.

03:32.046 --> 03:33.580
Okay, what time
are we now?

03:33.613 --> 03:36.050
- <i>Five, four, three...</i>
- Hope! Hope!

03:36.083 --> 03:37.885
<i>...two, one.</i>

03:37.919 --> 03:39.586
Cue hype woman.

03:39.619 --> 03:40.687
Harry!

03:40.721 --> 03:42.555
- Hope!
- Harry!

03:47.128 --> 03:50.630
Ladies and gentlemen,
are you ready for some hope in your life?

03:50.664 --> 03:52.066
That's it, volunteers.

03:52.099 --> 03:54.802
The man,
the myth, the legend,

03:54.835 --> 03:59.707
Harry Hope!

03:59.740 --> 04:01.776
Beautiful people of London.

04:01.809 --> 04:04.477
In four days' time,

04:04.511 --> 04:06.747
the world will come together

04:06.781 --> 04:11.085
for the biggest peace gig
known to mankind.

04:11.118 --> 04:14.688
Whoo!

04:17.959 --> 04:19.860
The power of music
will stop this war.

04:19.894 --> 04:24.799
The unifying power of music
will stop this war!

04:26.633 --> 04:28.002
<i>Pump your fist.</i>

04:31.604 --> 04:32.974
I call upon the leaders...

04:33.007 --> 04:36.509
I call upon the leaders
of the world to tune in

04:36.543 --> 04:41.182
and listen to what four
billion people have to say!

04:41.215 --> 04:42.883
Yes!

04:42.917 --> 04:45.119
Stop the war!
Stop the war!

04:45.152 --> 04:45.987
<i>Let the volunteers
rush the stage.</i>

04:46.020 --> 04:47.188
No, no, no, let 'em in,
let 'em in.

04:47.221 --> 04:49.790
Come on... Let them, it's fine.
Come on, let them through.

04:49.824 --> 04:51.292
Come on, you, come, come.

04:51.325 --> 04:52.692
- You see, guys, it's...
- Okay.

04:52.727 --> 04:54.195
It's not about me, it's...

04:57.597 --> 04:59.900
it's about...
it's about these guys.

05:01.035 --> 05:03.304
You know, I'm...

05:03.337 --> 05:05.206
- I'm pretty much like the, uh...
- Cut the ginger.

05:05.239 --> 05:07.908
Out my way.
Okay, shh, I'm coming.

05:07.942 --> 05:09.642
I'm... I'm just the...

05:11.812 --> 05:14.647
You know how a duck flies
and the head of it,

05:14.681 --> 05:15.750
- it migrates?
- Yeah?

05:15.783 --> 05:18.618
- You ever played Duck Hunt before?
- Yeah!

05:18.651 --> 05:20.687
Kate, hijab hipster
on your right.

05:20.721 --> 05:21.856
Got it, got it.

05:21.889 --> 05:23.290
I'm not the dog,
I'm the duck.

05:23.324 --> 05:26.060
He's not the dog,
he's the duck!

05:26.093 --> 05:28.829
Three, two, one,
off you go.

05:28.863 --> 05:29.897
Fuck off.

05:29.930 --> 05:31.298
Ginger eliminated.

05:32.033 --> 05:34.601
- Go ahead.
- Okay, sing a song.

05:35.668 --> 05:39.106
<i>♪ Hope is dope ♪</i>

05:39.140 --> 05:42.609
<i>♪ Hope is dope ♪</i>

05:42.642 --> 05:46.013
<i>♪ You can cope ♪</i>

05:46.047 --> 05:48.983
<i>♪ Hope is dope ♪</i>

05:49.016 --> 05:52.086
<i>♪ I'm saying hope
is dope Motherfucker, yeah ♪</i>

05:52.119 --> 05:54.621
<i>♪ I'm saying hope is dope
Motherfucker, yeah ♪</i>

05:54.654 --> 05:56.991
<i>♪ I'm saying hope is dope
Motherfucker, yeah ♪</i>

05:57.024 --> 05:59.592
<i>♪ I'm saying hope is dope
Motherfucker, yeah ♪</i>

05:59.927 --> 06:01.694
Peace...

06:01.729 --> 06:05.800
Um... Simon,
my sister has arrived from...

06:05.833 --> 06:07.334
Throop in Dorset.

06:07.368 --> 06:09.837
Can you keep her occupied? I don't want
to see her until after the concert.

06:09.870 --> 06:11.638
I could put her
on the phones.

06:12.339 --> 06:13.640
Peace.

06:14.041 --> 06:15.209
No.

06:15.242 --> 06:17.644
- Envelope stuffing?
- No.

06:17.978 --> 06:19.679
Coffee.

06:19.713 --> 06:21.949
Cold drinks. Maybe she can
hold cold drinks.

06:21.982 --> 06:26.220
Because we want
to end this war!

06:28.722 --> 06:30.991
Harry, Harry!
It's a ceasefire!

06:31.025 --> 06:32.960
<i>The war is over.</i>

06:32.993 --> 06:34.128
<i>We now go live to Ukbar,</i>

06:34.161 --> 06:37.765
<i>where the governor is making
the shock announcement.</i>

06:37.798 --> 06:39.900
<i>The ceasefire
between our two nations</i>

06:39.934 --> 06:41.302
<i>will come into effect.</i>

06:42.336 --> 06:44.939
Make this go away.
Just... just make it go away.

06:44.972 --> 06:46.774
Make peace go away?

06:46.807 --> 06:48.776
Yes. You make
other things go away.

06:48.809 --> 06:50.010
Why can't you
make this go away?

06:50.044 --> 06:52.246
This isn't a story, Harry,
it's, um,

06:52.279 --> 06:55.216
two sovereign nations
with armies.

06:55.249 --> 06:57.051
This is my chance
at a Nobel Peace Prize!

06:57.084 --> 06:58.752
Both sides declared
the ceasefire, Harry.

06:58.786 --> 07:02.223
I've got Grammys, BRITs,
Tonys, Oscars!

07:02.256 --> 07:03.958
I... I wanna be
a world leader!

07:03.991 --> 07:05.359
A global humanitarian!

07:05.392 --> 07:07.660
Mandela, Gandhi!

07:07.694 --> 07:10.397
I can't do that without stopping a
war, Kate. This is my time!

07:10.431 --> 07:11.999
What are they talking about?

07:12.533 --> 07:14.001
I've no idea.

07:14.034 --> 07:17.204
Hi! I'm Peggy.
I'm Kate's sister.

07:17.238 --> 07:19.006
And her new PA.

07:19.907 --> 07:21.308
I'm Kate's PA.

07:22.977 --> 07:24.145
Oh.

07:25.913 --> 07:28.015
What are you looking at?

07:28.048 --> 07:29.216
Um, shall we get a coffee?

07:29.250 --> 07:30.718
Yeah, let's get a coffee.

07:33.988 --> 07:37.057
I've got four billion people
waiting for peace, Kate.

07:37.091 --> 07:39.160
Four billion people
waiting for peace!

07:39.193 --> 07:41.028
Why can't he wait
until Saturday?

07:41.061 --> 07:43.931
Damn, after Saturday he can
have all the peace he wants.

07:46.233 --> 07:47.401
That's it.

07:48.802 --> 07:50.971
We don't need to
call off the ceasefire,

07:51.005 --> 07:54.141
we just need a few more
days of skirmishes.

07:54.175 --> 07:56.710
Just skirmishes
on the border.

07:56.744 --> 07:58.112
I'm... I'm not following.

07:58.145 --> 08:00.181
We just need three more days of
fake news coming out of Georgia,

08:00.214 --> 08:02.149
to make it look like
the war's still on.

08:02.183 --> 08:04.285
Then you do the concert
on Saturday,

08:04.318 --> 08:05.452
then we can have peace.

08:05.486 --> 08:07.054
- Thanks to me.
- All thanks to you.

08:07.087 --> 08:08.255
Great! Good.

08:08.289 --> 08:09.757
You better get out there
and get on it.

08:09.790 --> 08:11.258
- Sorry?
- Georgia!

08:11.292 --> 08:13.894
I need you to go out there
and start up some skirmishes,

08:13.928 --> 08:16.931
with CNN, BBC,
all the major news outlets,

08:16.964 --> 08:18.465
whoever the hell
you need to get.

08:18.499 --> 08:21.135
You're always saying that one
image can change the world.

08:21.168 --> 08:23.804
And so...

08:23.837 --> 08:27.141
I want those screens
filled with despair.

08:27.174 --> 08:28.909
Yeah.

08:28.943 --> 08:30.844
Yeah, you can't have
hope without despair.

08:30.878 --> 08:32.746
Mmm. I'm testing that theory
right now.

08:32.780 --> 08:35.015
Rape! Planes!

08:35.049 --> 08:36.250
Images of death!

08:36.283 --> 08:37.451
Dead kittens!

08:37.484 --> 08:38.919
The puppies
that can't get adopted.

08:38.953 --> 08:40.453
Okay? Whatever the hell
you need to do,

08:40.486 --> 08:42.056
just make it happen.

08:43.357 --> 08:44.491
Okay.

08:46.860 --> 08:48.762
Oh, and if you don't,
you're fired.

08:50.097 --> 08:51.298
Why Japan?

08:51.332 --> 08:52.900
'Cause they meditate
with the cows.

08:52.933 --> 08:54.768
Matt, hand all press liaison
over to Marie.

08:54.802 --> 08:57.171
Simon, hand all artist liaison
over to Ravier.

08:57.204 --> 09:00.808
Rape, planes, images of murder,
all the good stuff.

09:00.841 --> 09:03.410
For the next three days, we push
the line that this war is still on.

09:03.444 --> 09:05.179
Well, who's handling this
for us?

09:05.212 --> 09:06.347
We are.

09:06.380 --> 09:09.917
Yeah,
we run red carpets and press junkets.

09:09.950 --> 09:11.452
What do we know about war?

09:12.353 --> 09:13.821
Enough to fake one.

09:29.536 --> 09:30.838
Hello.

09:35.976 --> 09:37.778
Can I help
with anything?

09:39.313 --> 09:40.414
Can I help?

09:42.182 --> 09:43.550
Can I help with anything?

09:43.584 --> 09:45.386
Of course,
you're her new PA.

09:45.419 --> 09:48.455
Book us all flights.
All of us to Tbilisi.

09:58.432 --> 09:59.466
Hello?

09:59.500 --> 10:00.934
Taxi!

10:06.106 --> 10:08.108
Move back, move back.

10:20.187 --> 10:22.156
Uh, it's this way.
This way.

10:37.404 --> 10:39.006
This is it, this is the gate.

10:39.473 --> 10:40.474
Come on!

10:41.375 --> 10:42.910
Guys, come on!

10:42.943 --> 10:45.312
Those two, uh, him and him.

10:46.013 --> 10:47.147
And that's yours.

10:48.582 --> 10:50.551
This place is really big.
Have a nice flight.

10:50.584 --> 10:52.186
Thank you.

10:52.219 --> 10:54.388
He needs to go with this line for
the news at 10:00. The ceasefire is...

10:54.421 --> 10:56.223
- Excuse me.
- The ceasefire is...

10:56.256 --> 10:58.025
Miss, excuse me.

10:58.058 --> 11:00.394
Turn off your phone,
please. Now.

11:00.427 --> 11:02.096
I'll call you
when I land.

11:10.070 --> 11:11.338
I've never been
on a plane before.

11:11.372 --> 11:12.506
What are you doing?

11:12.539 --> 11:13.974
Trying to make
this seat go back.

11:14.007 --> 11:15.542
What are you doing
on the plane?

11:17.044 --> 11:18.112
Simon...

11:19.313 --> 11:20.514
Peggy's on the plane.

11:20.547 --> 11:21.648
Free peanuts.

11:21.682 --> 11:23.350
Why are you on the plane?

11:23.384 --> 11:24.585
You said to
book us all flights.

11:24.618 --> 11:27.221
I said book us all flights.

11:27.254 --> 11:29.289
You went like that.
I thought I was in the circle.

11:29.323 --> 11:30.457
Sit down.
We are taking off.

11:30.491 --> 11:33.260
No, it was a clerical error.
We don't want her with us.

11:33.293 --> 11:34.461
Sit down, please.

11:34.495 --> 11:36.096
- I've done it!
- Can we stop it?

11:36.130 --> 11:37.464
Mister, please!

11:37.498 --> 11:39.466
Oh, it's a disaster.

11:56.049 --> 11:57.418
Ooh, a shelf.

11:58.720 --> 12:00.387
Oh, you've got one too.

12:05.092 --> 12:06.693
Why are we going to Georgia?

12:06.728 --> 12:10.230
I am going to Georgia to
shoot some documentary footage

12:10.264 --> 12:11.498
for the concert.

12:11.532 --> 12:13.701
You are going to go straight
back home as soon as we land.

12:15.169 --> 12:17.204
Well, if there's
anything you need...

12:17.237 --> 12:18.405
I need silence.

12:20.140 --> 12:21.442
This is crazy.

12:23.076 --> 12:26.246
Look, Kate knows exactly
what she's doing.

12:26.280 --> 12:29.483
We're going to a warzone
and I'm wearing slip-ons.

12:29.516 --> 12:31.985
<i>Reports from the CIA
suggest Ukbar</i>

12:32.019 --> 12:34.221
<i>may have already
broken the ceasefire.</i>

12:34.254 --> 12:35.422
<i>Where's the evidence?</i>

12:35.456 --> 12:39.159
<i>Just a series of websites
that have no credibility.</i>

12:39.193 --> 12:42.062
<i>We haven't seen any new
images of war from the region.</i>

12:50.070 --> 12:53.240
<i>Ladies and
gentlemen, welcome to Tugdidi Airport.</i>

12:53.574 --> 12:55.476
Excuse me.

12:55.509 --> 12:56.677
Did he say Tugdidi Airport?

12:56.711 --> 12:59.480
We were
diverted because of the crisis.

13:01.515 --> 13:03.217
Where's Tugdidi?

13:08.188 --> 13:10.390
The CIA has quoted
our BuzzFeed story.

13:10.424 --> 13:13.494
Yes. They've already
fed it to Fox News.

13:13.527 --> 13:14.729
Our driver's in Tbilisi.

13:14.762 --> 13:16.563
How are we meant
to get to Kazbegi now?

13:16.597 --> 13:18.265
We're meant to be
on the frontline.

13:18.298 --> 13:19.466
Well, Uber.

13:20.100 --> 13:21.134
MyTaxi.

13:24.505 --> 13:26.440
Urgh. Unbelievable.

13:28.509 --> 13:31.411
All the flights are grounded.
I'm gonna have to stick with you guys.

13:31.445 --> 13:33.146
I can book her into a hotel

13:33.180 --> 13:34.681
until they start
flying out again.

13:34.716 --> 13:36.483
You can stay here,
can't you?

13:36.517 --> 13:38.085
Yeah? Be okay?

13:38.118 --> 13:39.286
Yeah?

13:41.255 --> 13:42.489
No, she'll have to
come with us.

13:42.523 --> 13:43.758
- No, I can book her...
- She's coming with me,

13:43.791 --> 13:45.058
where I can keep
an eye on her.

13:45.092 --> 13:46.293
Don't tell Mum, okay?

13:46.326 --> 13:48.262
Ooh, it's just so exciting!

13:48.295 --> 13:51.331
Will one of you sort
some bloody transport now?

13:53.634 --> 13:55.469
Harry, hi.

13:55.502 --> 13:56.537
<i>Where the hell are you?</i>

13:56.570 --> 13:58.405
Well, um, I don't know,
'cause we got diverted.

13:58.438 --> 14:00.541
We need images, Kate.
Footage of the war.

14:00.574 --> 14:01.809
Stop pissing around.

14:01.843 --> 14:03.644
You have 96 hours
to fix this.

14:03.677 --> 14:05.279
I only landed
half an hour ago, so...

14:05.312 --> 14:07.114
If I don't get that
Nobel Peace Prize,

14:07.147 --> 14:08.682
I will hold you
personally responsible.

14:08.716 --> 14:10.117
Get it done!

14:10.150 --> 14:11.385
<i>Now I have to go.</i>

14:11.418 --> 14:13.320
I'm playing poker
with the Dalai Lama

14:13.353 --> 14:14.756
and he cheats like a...

14:17.859 --> 14:19.626
Well?

14:19.660 --> 14:21.562
Auntie Kate?

14:21.595 --> 14:24.231
Don't tell me you're
taking a bloody selfie.

14:24.264 --> 14:26.099
- Auntie Kate?
- What?

14:26.133 --> 14:30.504
Uh, this man here says he'll
take us to Kazbegi for 300 lari.

14:30.537 --> 14:32.506
Is that a lot?
It sounds like a lot.

14:33.407 --> 14:35.676
Uh, hello.
Hello, hi.

14:36.577 --> 14:38.545
Hi. Uh, we need to go here.

14:39.479 --> 14:41.648
To the frontline, yeah?

14:41.682 --> 14:44.251
Um, I'll pay you.
Me pay you.

14:44.284 --> 14:46.153
No, okay, well,
tell him I'll pay him.

14:46.186 --> 14:48.589
I'll pay him 2,000 lari.

14:49.222 --> 14:52.092
2,000 laris.

14:52.827 --> 14:53.828
Yes?

14:54.494 --> 14:56.263
Okay, yes,
he says yes, yes.

15:11.813 --> 15:13.347
When we get
where we're going, Peggy,

15:13.380 --> 15:14.749
I want you to stay in the car.

15:16.183 --> 15:17.819
I'm gonna stay
in the car too.

15:17.852 --> 15:19.252
I think I might too.

15:19.286 --> 15:20.454
- No, you're coming.
- I don't want to.

15:20.487 --> 15:22.556
I think this is crazy.
There, I said it.

15:22.589 --> 15:23.624
You'll do it because
it's your job.

15:23.657 --> 15:26.226
I didn't sign up for going
into a warzone, okay?

15:26.259 --> 15:28.730
We didn't even go to T in the
Park because it's too dangerous.

15:28.763 --> 15:29.931
And now we're going
to a frontline?

15:29.964 --> 15:31.498
Don't push me on this, Matt!

16:15.910 --> 16:18.378
Kate Hemmings,
I'm Manu, the fixer.

16:18.412 --> 16:20.480
Manu. Simon Boggan.

16:20.514 --> 16:24.217
We were diverted to Tugdidi.
Nightmare.

16:24.251 --> 16:26.821
Okay, what we need is, um,

16:27.387 --> 16:29.556
is footage of soldiers,

16:29.589 --> 16:32.392
if we can get some tanks
or artillery moving,

16:32.426 --> 16:34.361
doesn't matter which way,
we can edit round that.

16:34.394 --> 16:36.798
But what we need
is kinetic images,

16:36.831 --> 16:39.332
uh, fog of war and all that.

16:39.366 --> 16:40.667
Distressed locals.

16:41.969 --> 16:45.238
The Ukbars, they pulled out
since ceasefire.

16:45.272 --> 16:46.774
Oh, okay.

16:46.808 --> 16:48.009
What about the Georgian army?

16:48.042 --> 16:49.676
Well, they pulled back too.

16:49.711 --> 16:51.813
You know, the part
of peace negotiation.

16:51.846 --> 16:53.280
Distressed locals?

17:03.690 --> 17:05.727
This is meant to be the...
the frontline.

17:05.760 --> 17:07.560
You said yesterday
this was the frontline.

17:07.594 --> 17:09.463
Well, it was. But then
they called the ceasefire.

17:09.496 --> 17:11.531
Oh, this is a bloody disaster.

17:11.565 --> 17:12.733
Take us to the hotel.

17:24.544 --> 17:26.848
There's not many
places to stay around here,

17:26.881 --> 17:29.616
so you have to stay
in my cousin's rooms.

17:30.684 --> 17:33.054
This is the best hotel
in Kazbegi.

17:33.087 --> 17:36.423
All rooms are booked,
but I pulled some strings.

17:55.475 --> 17:58.545
We are booked up,
but we have this.

17:59.412 --> 18:01.414
Okay.

18:01.448 --> 18:03.316
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

18:03.350 --> 18:05.019
And this one is for ladies.

