40:05.106 --> 40:07.607
Oh, God. Oh, no.

40:15.316 --> 40:16.350
Ugh.

40:25.025 --> 40:26.127
Ugh!

40:32.466 --> 40:33.968
Is it true?

40:36.203 --> 40:38.172
Your mum and dad
are your parents,

40:38.205 --> 40:39.340
that's all you need to know.

40:41.842 --> 40:43.878
What happened?

40:43.911 --> 40:45.279
I'll never replace your mum.

40:45.312 --> 40:47.781
I know that.

40:47.815 --> 40:50.251
You... you'd be a terrible mum.

40:57.291 --> 40:58.959
What happened then?

41:00.327 --> 41:02.796
Who's my biological dad?

41:06.500 --> 41:08.736
He was a seasonal worker...

41:10.237 --> 41:11.872
on Hopkins Farm.

41:13.807 --> 41:15.109
I was 15.

41:16.043 --> 41:17.411
It was one night,

41:19.046 --> 41:20.281
in a barn.

41:21.949 --> 41:25.319
By the time I realized
I was pregnant, he was gone.

41:26.187 --> 41:27.788
What happened then?

41:30.491 --> 41:32.293
I had to tell my mum.

41:35.863 --> 41:36.964
Which was awful.

41:38.065 --> 41:39.867
The worst day of my life.

41:39.900 --> 41:42.469
And so my mum,
sort of, took over.

41:42.503 --> 41:44.205
She made up the story.

41:44.238 --> 41:47.808
She put a cushion
under her clothes

41:47.841 --> 41:49.910
and I was sent away
for a few months.

41:51.445 --> 41:53.047
When you were born,

41:56.083 --> 41:58.052
Mum came and that was it.

42:01.522 --> 42:03.357
It must've been awful for you.

42:07.161 --> 42:08.362
It was.

42:11.265 --> 42:12.433
It was.

42:15.536 --> 42:17.171
I've never done this with...

42:18.572 --> 42:19.807
my other mum.

42:22.109 --> 42:23.944
What should I call you now?

42:24.511 --> 42:25.746
Bollocks.

42:44.999 --> 42:46.267
Oh, thank you.

42:48.068 --> 42:49.470
That's great, thank you.

42:52.072 --> 42:53.240
Thank you.

42:55.576 --> 43:00.047
Oh, yeah, once these are dry,
we can set off.

43:00.080 --> 43:02.216
- There are no streetlights.
- We need to get out of here.

43:03.951 --> 43:05.252
It's pitch back out there.

43:05.286 --> 43:07.087
We'll have to wait
until morning.

43:09.356 --> 43:11.992
Okay, tomorrow
we can walk around

43:12.026 --> 43:14.094
and we can find
somewhere with Internet,

43:14.128 --> 43:15.062
we'll get hold of Manu

43:15.095 --> 43:16.997
and he can get us the hell
out of Georgia.

43:17.031 --> 43:18.032
Hmm.

43:18.465 --> 43:20.167
Excuse me, um,

43:20.200 --> 43:22.269
do you have
an iPhone 8 charger?

43:24.238 --> 43:25.839
'Cause mine's run
out of battery.

43:31.178 --> 43:34.048
No, of course not.
It's a silly question.

43:34.081 --> 43:36.350
Just wondered.

43:39.453 --> 43:40.954
Ugh.

43:48.062 --> 43:50.364
Goal!

43:50.397 --> 43:52.366
"I am deeply sorry

43:53.901 --> 43:57.871
to have to tell you that
there's been an accident

43:58.539 --> 44:01.342
and Matt has been shot

44:02.343 --> 44:05.079
whilst taking stills

44:05.112 --> 44:06.947
for our latest campaign."

44:06.980 --> 44:08.115
What?

44:08.982 --> 44:10.017
It's just...

44:10.050 --> 44:11.518
- Go on, what?
- I dunno.

44:11.552 --> 44:14.121
Well, I'm in the
middle of it, so...

44:16.123 --> 44:18.125
Why not make it
sound like he was brave?

44:18.158 --> 44:20.961
This is stressful enough
without notes.

44:23.964 --> 44:26.300
I dunno. If it was me,
I'd like you to tell Mum

44:26.333 --> 44:29.002
that I died
doing something brave.

44:30.037 --> 44:32.106
- Don't say that.
- Well...

44:34.141 --> 44:36.009
You said his parents
were proud, right?

44:36.043 --> 44:37.644
Hmm.

44:37.678 --> 44:39.413
So, why not give them
one last thing

44:39.446 --> 44:40.614
to be proud of him for?

44:42.616 --> 44:43.617
Here.

44:48.122 --> 44:51.558
"On a film shoot

44:51.592 --> 44:55.295
in a forest in Georgia,

44:55.329 --> 45:01.068
Matt and his team
got caught in firefight.

45:06.741 --> 45:10.644
<i>He was the only one
not to panic.</i>

45:14.548 --> 45:16.250
<i>One by one,</i>

45:16.283 --> 45:19.486
<i>he made sure
all of us were safe,</i>

45:21.588 --> 45:24.224
<i>but then he realized</i>

45:24.258 --> 45:28.328
<i>the six-year-old refugee girl
was still in danger.</i>

45:28.362 --> 45:33.367
<i>Despite all of us saying it
was too dangerous to go back,</i>

45:33.400 --> 45:35.569
<i>begging him to stay.</i>

45:35.602 --> 45:39.173
<i>Yes, despite us
begging him to stay,</i>

45:39.206 --> 45:41.308
<i>Matt ran to rescue the child."</i>

45:43.243 --> 45:44.244
<i>No.</i>

45:45.245 --> 45:46.413
<i>"Children.</i>

45:51.185 --> 45:55.022
<i>Once Matt was sure
they were safe,</i>

45:55.055 --> 45:57.691
<i>he allowed his injuries
to take hold of him...</i>

46:01.261 --> 46:02.396
<i>and he died.</i>

46:09.336 --> 46:10.637
<i>His last words were..."</i>

46:11.706 --> 46:14.742
Tell Mum and Dad I love them

46:14.776 --> 46:16.210
and I'm sorry.

46:16.243 --> 46:17.244
No.

46:20.581 --> 46:24.084
<i>Tell Mum and Dad
and Peggy and Kate</i>

46:24.117 --> 46:26.019
I love them,

46:26.053 --> 46:27.521
and thank you for everything.

46:28.823 --> 46:32.025
Oh, that's a great story.

46:32.693 --> 46:33.994
I know.

46:34.929 --> 46:37.297
It's a shame
to waste it on the parents.

46:51.311 --> 46:52.546
It's a great story.

46:56.851 --> 46:59.086
Yeah. Yeah, Harry?

46:59.721 --> 47:01.154
Yeah, where are you?

47:01.856 --> 47:03.357
Okay, stay right where you are.

47:03.390 --> 47:05.292
I'm coming to you, yeah?

47:05.325 --> 47:08.095
Oh, we've got complete control
of the story.

47:08.128 --> 47:10.597
Oh, yeah. Okay, bye.

47:12.867 --> 47:15.703
The nation mourns the passing
of Matt Townsley.

47:15.737 --> 47:18.438
WNN is at the family home,
to hear Harry Hope

47:18.472 --> 47:20.173
<i>pay tribute to this brave
young man now.</i>

47:20.207 --> 47:21.843
Good evening,
ladies and gentlemen.

47:21.876 --> 47:23.811
May I present
Veronica Townsley

47:23.845 --> 47:26.446
and rock legend Harry Hope.

47:26.480 --> 47:30.284
Listen, he was...
he was so selfless. He was.

47:30.317 --> 47:32.085
It was typical of the Matt
that I knew

47:32.119 --> 47:34.488
that he died helping others.

47:34.521 --> 47:36.323
That's why in 48 hours

47:36.356 --> 47:39.426
we're putting on the world's
biggest concert for peace.

47:39.459 --> 47:41.796
<i>We need it now more than ever.</i>

47:41.829 --> 47:44.298
<i>Don't do it for me,
do it for Matt.</i>

47:44.331 --> 47:45.532
Mathaniel.

47:46.099 --> 47:48.468
He always smelled of rose

47:48.502 --> 47:50.337
and he looks like
Terrence Howard, look at him.

47:50.370 --> 47:53.440
He's got green eyes
that you can get lost in.

47:53.473 --> 47:55.843
He's got Caucasian eyes
on a black body, that's rare.

47:55.877 --> 47:57.477
Do it for him.

47:59.847 --> 48:02.750
What's he saying?
What's he saying?

48:04.451 --> 48:05.753
He says he can't get
a car to us,

48:05.787 --> 48:07.120
they've closed the roads,

48:07.154 --> 48:09.356
but if we follow the river
south to Bagero,

48:09.389 --> 48:11.558
there's a UNICEF camp,

48:11.592 --> 48:13.293
and he'll arrange transport
for us from there.

48:13.327 --> 48:15.629
Okay.

48:15.662 --> 48:17.431
Okay, we can set off
tomorrow morning

48:17.464 --> 48:20.267
and get you back
to Throop in Dorset

48:20.868 --> 48:22.636
and the farm,

48:22.669 --> 48:25.238
and you can forget
about all this.

48:25.807 --> 48:26.808
Great.

48:28.776 --> 48:30.344
Mathaniel Townsley:

48:30.377 --> 48:33.547
journalist, humanitarian, hero.

48:38.385 --> 48:40.687
Mr. Governor,
why was Mathaniel shot

48:40.722 --> 48:42.589
when he was trying
to save children?

48:44.191 --> 48:47.494
What kind of journalist wears
a military uniform?

48:48.395 --> 48:49.630
He's a spy.

48:50.732 --> 48:53.166
<i>Alleged war criminal
Matt Townsley</i>

48:53.200 --> 48:54.802
is accused of torture
and murder,

48:54.836 --> 48:56.938
as shocking pictures
emerge on the Internet.

49:03.077 --> 49:04.879
Mr. <i>Hope,</i>
<i>Matt Townsley worked for you.</i>

49:04.912 --> 49:06.246
Why was he out there?

49:06.279 --> 49:08.448
Harry, no. No. No.

49:08.482 --> 49:10.752
Okay, that's top secret
and, um,

49:10.785 --> 49:13.286
I'm not at liberty to divulge
that type of information.

49:13.320 --> 49:15.322
Was he spying
on the Ukbar military?

49:15.355 --> 49:16.724
- Yep!
- No.

49:16.758 --> 49:18.793
All right,
don't forget, people,

49:18.826 --> 49:21.194
best concert that
you ever gonna see,

49:21.228 --> 49:22.362
<i>in two days.</i>

49:22.396 --> 49:24.398
<i>For peace, right?</i>

49:26.366 --> 49:29.536
Again, this spy
is concrete evidence

49:29.569 --> 49:32.439
of British efforts
to undermine our state.

49:33.975 --> 49:36.176
The ceasefire is over.

49:37.544 --> 49:40.647
Ukbar is at war with Georgia.

49:51.558 --> 49:53.527
Harry.

49:53.560 --> 49:54.829
<i>What the hell
have you done, Kate?</i>

49:54.862 --> 49:56.329
<i>You started World War III!</i>

49:56.363 --> 49:59.399
What? No, I was just
on the toilet.

49:59.433 --> 50:00.968
I said skirmishes!

50:01.002 --> 50:03.670
You know what a skirmish is,
don't you? A skirmish?

50:03.705 --> 50:05.740
Skirmish? Can you stop
saying "skirmish"?

50:05.773 --> 50:07.441
That story that you
put out about Matt?

50:07.474 --> 50:09.944
Now America is sending
troops into Georgia.

50:09.977 --> 50:12.013
- What are you talking about?
- <i>Ground troops!</i>

50:12.046 --> 50:14.749
Boots on the ground!
It's a full-scale invasion!

50:14.782 --> 50:16.718
<i>And the Europeans
are on the other side.</i>

50:16.751 --> 50:18.920
<i>That's Americans and British,</i>

50:18.953 --> 50:21.856
<i>husbands and sons,
all fighting!</i>

50:21.889 --> 50:23.791
Nobody wants a peace
concert anymore!

50:23.825 --> 50:25.392
Everybody wants to win!

50:25.425 --> 50:26.493
Kate!

50:26.526 --> 50:28.695
<i>I'll never win
a Nobel Prize now!</i>

50:28.730 --> 50:30.998
- Come quick!
- <i>Kate! Where you going?</i>

50:31.032 --> 50:32.632
<i>You have fucked up my life,</i>

50:32.666 --> 50:34.234
and now I'm gonna fuck yours!

50:36.070 --> 50:38.472
Limo driver, pull over
and give me some head.

50:40.507 --> 50:42.576
No! No, no, no.

50:42.609 --> 50:44.779
No, no, no!

50:45.345 --> 50:46.748
No, no!

50:48.950 --> 50:51.551
No, no, no! No!

50:53.553 --> 50:55.790
No, I can't start a war!

50:56.556 --> 50:57.792
No.

50:57.825 --> 51:00.027
This is great though,
this is exactly what we wanted!

51:00.061 --> 51:02.395
Hello! Hi! No, no, no.

51:02.429 --> 51:03.497
Hi. Hello.

51:05.032 --> 51:06.701
There's been a bit of a mix-up.

51:08.069 --> 51:10.004
There's actually no war
going on.

51:11.139 --> 51:13.975
So you're not needed.
Do you mind turning around?

51:14.008 --> 51:15.642
Turn around now.

51:15.675 --> 51:17.310
Do you speak English?

51:17.344 --> 51:18.478
He doesn't even speak English.

51:22.449 --> 51:24.484
Ah, thank you.

51:24.518 --> 51:27.454
Hello. Finally,
someone in charge.

51:27.487 --> 51:29.757
Well, there's been, um,
a bit of a mix-up basically,

51:29.791 --> 51:30.892
and just a clerical error!

51:40.001 --> 51:41.836
It's okay, come on.

51:41.869 --> 51:42.937
Over here.

51:43.938 --> 51:44.972
Come on.

51:54.715 --> 51:56.316
I only sent an email.

51:57.484 --> 51:59.586
- We sent an email.
- This is ridiculous.

51:59.619 --> 52:01.621
This should not be allowed to happen.

52:01.655 --> 52:03.456
Someone should be checking
this kind of stuff.

52:03.490 --> 52:05.026
It's ridiculous
this can happen.

52:23.610 --> 52:24.611
Wow.

52:42.596 --> 52:44.464
Oh, now what?

52:47.902 --> 52:49.904
Oh... what do they want?

52:53.107 --> 52:55.442
Oh.

52:55.475 --> 52:59.080
- I think they think you're some kind of leader.
- Oh, my gosh.

53:04.484 --> 53:05.720
Um...

53:06.653 --> 53:08.588
So... Sorry, what?

53:08.622 --> 53:10.657
He says you've made him
feel very happy,

53:10.690 --> 53:12.093
and he will fight for you.

53:14.128 --> 53:16.463
Oh, no, no, no, no.

53:16.496 --> 53:17.865
No, there's no war,

53:17.899 --> 53:20.835
so go back to farming

53:20.868 --> 53:22.569
or whatever it is you do.

53:31.611 --> 53:34.547
No, he says you're the
chosen leader of the Georgian resistance.

53:36.017 --> 53:38.152
Well, I... I'm...

53:38.185 --> 53:40.721
I'm not the leader
of the resistance,

53:40.755 --> 53:43.124
I just handle publicity
and events.

53:43.157 --> 53:44.792
Um...

53:46.093 --> 53:48.930
But... see you later.

53:50.831 --> 53:52.565
- Help me get down.
- Yeah.

53:52.599 --> 53:54.601
- See you in a bit.
- Thank you.

53:54.634 --> 53:55.937
Thank you so much.

53:55.970 --> 53:57.805
- Thank you!
- Right.

53:59.040 --> 54:01.175
Run, run, run. Run.

54:02.977 --> 54:04.779
Thank you so much.

54:13.687 --> 54:15.723
Ah, I hope Manu is
true to his word,

54:15.756 --> 54:17.792
because if we get to Bagero and he's not there...

54:17.825 --> 54:19.093
...I don't know how we're
gonna get out of here.

54:19.126 --> 54:20.694
Oh, Kate.

54:20.728 --> 54:22.462
- Kate.
- Huh?

54:23.097 --> 54:25.465
Oh, for God's sake!

54:30.037 --> 54:32.073
- Shoo!
- Er, Kate. Kate.

54:32.106 --> 54:33.808
- Shoo!
- Kate!

54:33.841 --> 54:34.875
Shoo! Shoo!

54:34.909 --> 54:38.980
Kate... they could be...

54:39.013 --> 54:42.049
I dunno, they could be
kind of useful.

54:42.083 --> 54:44.684
You know, we might be able
to use them.

54:44.719 --> 54:46.686
They'll know the way to Bagero.

54:49.622 --> 54:51.826
- Bagero!
- Bagero?

54:52.927 --> 54:54.295
Fast, take us there.

54:54.328 --> 54:55.528
Yes.

54:55.863 --> 54:56.931
Great.

55:02.036 --> 55:05.006
We're watching this very
dangerous situation unfold

55:05.039 --> 55:08.142
<i>as US and European troops
prepare for all-out war.</i>

55:11.644 --> 55:12.913
- Harry.
- <i>Where the hell are you?</i>

55:12.947 --> 55:14.248
Listen, I know you sacked me

55:14.281 --> 55:16.217
and told me to go and die
in a fire,

55:16.250 --> 55:19.086
but listen, I have an idea
that might interest you.

55:21.989 --> 55:23.690
I know where Kate is.

55:28.829 --> 55:31.899
<i>You were
told not to start World War III!</i>

55:31.932 --> 55:34.068
- It's Harry Hope, sir.
- <i>Who do you think I am?</i>

55:34.101 --> 55:35.703
The pop star?

55:37.772 --> 55:39.740
- Mr. Hope.
- <i>Hi, Boris.</i>

55:39.774 --> 55:43.344
I have some information about a
propaganda campaign against you.

55:43.377 --> 55:46.914
Now, I don't know who
they're working for, but, uh,

55:46.947 --> 55:49.283
I do have their names
and last location.

55:49.316 --> 55:51.118
Why are you telling me this?

55:51.152 --> 55:52.153
If you can stop them,

55:52.186 --> 55:55.222
perhaps we can both have
the peace that we want.

55:55.256 --> 55:59.126
<i>I give her to you and in return,
we declare peace together.</i>

55:59.160 --> 56:01.929
- Go on.
- <i>Her name is Kate Hemming.</i>

56:01.962 --> 56:05.232
<i>She's outside a town called
Telavi in Georgia.</i>

56:05.266 --> 56:08.102
<i>I think a few years of POW
would do her good.</i>

56:09.669 --> 56:11.305
Thank you, Mr. Hope.

56:11.338 --> 56:13.274
I loved your last album.

56:14.375 --> 56:15.876
But not the new one.

56:19.646 --> 56:21.315
Get me the Georgians
on the phone.

56:43.170 --> 56:45.840
I've suddenly got
a massive wave of deja vu.

56:45.873 --> 56:47.607
- This place seems really familiar.
- Hmm?

56:48.175 --> 56:50.111
Oh, gosh, I'm exhausted.

56:50.144 --> 56:52.146
I could murder
a cup of tea.

56:54.815 --> 56:57.818
- Oh...
- Oh, God, we're in a warzone.

56:57.852 --> 56:59.787
What are you doing? Um...

57:01.922 --> 57:03.757
Wh... Um...

57:05.426 --> 57:06.827
Hello.

57:06.861 --> 57:08.262
Um, can we get past, please?

57:08.295 --> 57:10.064
We're trying
to head to Bagero.

57:10.097 --> 57:11.899
I think they think
we're trying to attack them.

57:15.903 --> 57:18.172
Stop, stop, stop!
Stop talking, everyone.

57:18.205 --> 57:19.206
Stop.

57:19.907 --> 57:20.908
Hi.

57:22.910 --> 57:24.078
Do you speak English?

57:24.945 --> 57:25.980
No?

57:26.013 --> 57:28.215
Hi. I'm, um...

57:28.249 --> 57:33.888
I'm the leader, uh,
of the Georgian resistance.

57:34.889 --> 57:38.826
So... queen, if you will.

57:38.859 --> 57:43.297
These people are my men,
and they will do as I say.

57:43.330 --> 57:46.167
No! Please, I'm doing my leader thing!

57:47.501 --> 57:50.070
We really need to get to Bagero,

57:50.104 --> 57:54.141
so if we put down our
weapons and declare peace,

57:54.175 --> 57:55.376
would you kindly
let us pass, please?

57:55.409 --> 57:57.444
It's really quite urgent.

57:57.478 --> 57:59.780
I'm the leader
and I declare peace.

57:59.813 --> 58:01.448
- Peace.
- Peace.

58:01.482 --> 58:03.284
No! I declare peace.

58:03.317 --> 58:04.952
Put down your fucking guns.

58:04.985 --> 58:07.221
Put your guns down
and your hands up.

58:07.254 --> 58:09.456
Gun... Put your bloody...
Put it on the fucking floor.

58:09.490 --> 58:11.158
Great. Hands up!

58:11.192 --> 58:12.359
Hands up!

58:12.393 --> 58:13.661
Guns down, hands up!

58:13.693 --> 58:16.696
See? It's a ceasefire.
They're gonna let us past. It's fine.

58:17.231 --> 58:18.732
Great.

58:18.766 --> 58:21.402
There, it's a ceasefire.

58:21.435 --> 58:22.836
How difficult was that?

58:37.952 --> 58:40.921
I think we confused peace
with surrender, you know?

58:42.423 --> 58:44.992
Can you not tell your mum
about this?

58:45.025 --> 58:46.193
She doesn't even know
that I'm here.

58:47.895 --> 58:49.797
You said she agreed to let
you come to the concert.

58:49.830 --> 58:50.864
Yeah, I lied.

58:52.099 --> 58:55.035
- Dear God.
- Yeah, I was ruthless.

58:55.069 --> 58:58.939
Anyway, you're my mum
and you said it was okay.

59:15.089 --> 59:16.156
What are they doing?

59:17.224 --> 59:18.459
Bite my blindfold.

59:22.563 --> 59:23.797
That's it.

59:26.433 --> 59:28.068
Let me see.
Let me see.

59:28.535 --> 59:30.004
Oh, come on.

59:33.073 --> 59:36.410
- Oh, what?
- They're playing football with the Georgians.

59:36.443 --> 59:39.847
It... It's like that game the British
and the Germans played in World War I.

